    <details>
        <description>
	    Discussion, feedback and even assessment takes place centred around a physical paper poster.
	    Students describe and explain their work with reference to the poster, often with multiple
	    sequential vistors (both tutors and other students).
	</description>
        <applicability>
	    Useful for divergent projects, where each student's work is different and required explaination and discussion	    
	</applicability>
        <consequences>
	    Disadvantages less confident and outgoing students and non first language speakers.
	    Can demotivate lower performing students.
	</consequences>
    </details>
    
